place.name: BAWSEY
place.gazetteerText: BAWSEY, a parish in Freebridge-Lynn district, Norfolk; 1½ mile NNW of Middleton r. station, and 3 ENE of King's-Lynn. Post Town, Lynn. Acres, 1,090. Real property, £549. Pop., 32. Houses, 5. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £55. Patron, A. Hammond, Esq. The church is in ruins. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
